Date: 12 July 2005 Theory and practice in parallel job scheduling Dror G. Feitelson Affiliated with Institute of Computer Science, The Hebrew University , Larry Rudolph Affiliated with Institute of Computer Science, The Hebrew University , Uwe Schwiegelshohn Affiliated with Computer Engineering Institute, University Dortmund , Kenneth C. Sevcik Affiliated with Department of Computer Science, University of Toronto , Parkson Wong Affiliated with MRJ, Inc., NASA Contract NAS 2-14303 The scheduling of jobs on parallel supercomputer is becoming the subject of much research. However, there is concern about the divergence of theory and practice. We review theoretical research in this area, and recommendations based on recent results. This is contrasted with a proposal for standard interfaces among the components of a scheduling system, that has grown from requirements in the field.